<TEXT>
spanish has replaced the yiddish and polish that 
filled the west side tenements where abe stolar grew up but the 
rundown buildings and littered streets still held their charm after 
58 years 
i didnt expect anything thats what keeps me young 
everything i get is a gift said the 77yearold chicago native 
returning to the neighborhood he left at age 19 for the soviet union 
accompanied by his sovietborn wife gita rozovskaya and sen 
paul simon dill who helped draw attention to the familys 
14year fight to leave the soviet union stolar explored the 
