mother 
gromyko who died sunday at the age of 79 was a fixture in world 
diplomacy since the time of josef stalin he helped forge the 
alliance that defeated nazi germany and the axis in world war ii 
joined in founding the united nations and participated in superpower 
talks some soviets have said gromyko shared the blame for foreign 
policy mistakes such as the 1979 soviet intervention in afghanistan 
he was foreign minister for 28 years was a member of the 
politburo and served as president a ceremonial post until 
gorbachev gave it new significance and took it for himself in 
october 
gorbachev gradually eased gromyko out of power as soviet foreign 
policy took a less confrontational approach in april gromyko lost 
his last post membership on the communist party central committee 
gorbachev gave a sober assessment of gromykos career monday 
saying it reflected our achievements our problems 
the cause of gromykos death was not announced but a soviet 
source said wednesday he had been hospitalized for three weeks and 
died of a burst aorta the bodys major artery he had been 
diagnosed as having circulatory problems five years ago said the 
source who spoke on condition of anonymity 
