on behalf of the nato alliance bush called last month for 
sweeping reductions in conventional forces in europe that would cut 
the number of us and soviet troops on the continent to 275000 for 
each superpower 
the soviets would have to remove 325000 men under the ceiling 
the americans would have to cut only 30000 
during nearly 10 hours of talks over two days gorbachev and 
mitterrand discussed reducing conventional forces and signed 22 
agreements covering cultural scientific business and military 
cooperation 
the statement on lebanon called for an immediate ceasefire 
rigorously respected as an indispensable condition for the 
establishment of a constructive interlebanese dialogue aiming at 
national reconciliation and peaceful building of a country founded 
on a balance of the interests of all lebanese communities 
the 14yearold civil war in lebanon a former french possession 
has pitted christians against moslems and druse militias since the 
latest outbreak of fighting in march druse forces and syrian troops 
in lebanon have battled the christian army of gen michel aoun aoun 
has demanded withdrawal of the syrians in lebanon under a 1976 
peacekeeping mandate 
moscow is the main arms supplier for syria as well as iraq which 
has been arming the christian forces 
gorbachev told reporters he supported a decision by the soviet 
writers union to publish alexander solzhenitsyns gulag 
archipelago and hinted that the exiled nobel literature laureate 
may have his soviet citizenship restored 
on wednesday morning gorbachev met with french intellectuals at 
the sorbonne and challenged them to help create a new more peaceful 
world 
he said the new soviet political and economic system he is 
fashioning would be a fusion of socialism and democracy its 
more difficult than we thought at the beginning but its working 
the country is changing rapidly and irreversibly 
