decades even its opponents said the party may have won more by 
losing in baja one of five states that voted sunday than it would 
have gained through victory 
this brings change to the sociopolitical reality not only in 
baja california but in all of mexico because it inspires confidence 
in their officials said ernesto ruffo who won the governorship 
for the national action party known by its initials pan 
ruffo said from his hometown of ensenada his victory was a step 
toward greater citizen participation in public decisions but pan 
president luis h alvarez said the pri was trying to cheat in the 
state legislature 
he said ruffo cannot govern encircled surrounded and pressured 
by an illegitimate legislature controlled by the pri alvarez 
addressed a rally outside the federal senate building in mexico city 
president carlos salinas de gortari was inaugurated dec 1 with a 
weak mandate because of his narrow victory in an election marred by 
fraud 
he won respect with efforts to revive the economy and fight 
endemic fraud and corruption but many viewed sundays state 
elections as a test of his intentions 
a mexico city shopkeeper who voted against salinas last year said 
he was impressed by the presidents performance and was willing to 
go back to the pri but only if it lost baja a pan stronghold 
pri officials claimed victory for candidate margarita ortega 
after the polls closed sunday night but appeared to back off in 
succeeding days party chairman luis donaldo colosio announced the 
concession late tuesday and official results are expected sunday 
it marks the beginning of a new step in the political life of 
the country a presidential spokeswoman said wednesday speaking 
privately 
pan figures showed ruffo winning by 204690 votes to 151099 
with ballots from 1073 of the 1168 polling booths counted 
the wellorganized conservative party made a major effort in 
baja where there is less opportunity for fraud at isolated 
countryside polling stations because most people live in a few 
cities near the us border 
party representatives obtained the official counts for most 
voting stations and roving squads of poll watchers were sent to 
trouble spots by radio 
crowds of pan supporters waving banners and beeping car horns 
celebrated into the morning hours in the baja california cities of 
mexicali tijuana and ensenada where ruffo served as mayor 
the pri was claiming mayoral victories in tijuana mexicali and 
tecate and a narrow majority in the state legislature it said 
there were voting irregularities on both sides but not serious 
enough to affect the results 
well have to learn how to live together in a new political 
relationship a federal government official said privately they 
have to learn how to govern we have to learn how to share power 
pan and the salinas administration have similar positions on many 
issues both are strongly against corruption and support free market 
economics 
in michoacan a western state the leftist democratic 
revolutionary party claimed it was being cheated of victory in state 
assembly elections colosio the pri chairman said his party was 
leading in 11 of 18 assembly districts 
ricardo pascoe pierce a spokesman for the leftist party said 
if they respect the vote in baja california and not in michoacan 
the pri would be trying to divide the opposition as well as the 
nations hope for democracy pri candidates won handily in state 
legislative elections in campeche and zacatecas the party claimed 
victory in chihuahua but the pan disputed that 
gubernatorial legislative and municipal elections were held in 
baja legislative and municipal in chihuahua and legislative in 
michoacan zacatecas and campeche 
most newspapers hailed the pri concession in baja california 
including the usually unsympathetic la jornada 
after saying we shouldnt applaud someone who simply complies 
with a duty dictated by the rules of competitive democracy la 
jornada added that the pri came out ahead because the defeat was 
such a contrast to its reputation for fraud 
