saying we have to distinguish between titos physical death and 
the symbolic death of titos political being whats happening today 
is the end of titos yugoslavia 
tito left yugoslavia with a highly decentralized system of 
collective leadership with diluted responsibilities the presidency 
for example rotates among leaders of its six peoples republics 
yugoslavias democratic and economic development largely 
depends on our ability to free ourselves from the tito cult 
djilas said in an interview with the belgrade weekly nin in may 
