frozen pork futures closed limitdown for the second consecutive 
session on the chicago mercantile exchange as the market continued 
to reel from last fridays quarterly agriculture department 
hogsandpigs inventory which showed fewer animals than the market 
had expected 
philip stanley an independent livestock trader said the 
porkbelly market was likely to drop the 2centsapound limit at 
the start of trading thursday because of a high number of unfilled 
sell orders 
live cattle futures rallied late in the session partly in line 
with the surging grain market and partly in a technical rebound from 
the losses it had sustained in sympathy with the pork market 
live cattle settled 78 cent to 128 cents higher with august at 
7060 cents a pound feeder cattle were 05 cent lower to 27 cent 
higher with august at 8062 cents a pound hogs were the limit 150 
cent lower to 115 cents higher with july at 4715 cents a pound 
frozen pork bellies were 2 cents lower across the board with july at 
3185 cents a pound 
raw coffee futures rebounded on new yorks coffee sugar amp cocoa 
exchange where prices had sunk to eightyear lows monday following 
the collapse of the international coffee organizations 
pricesupport system 
coffee settled 150 cents lower to 398 cents higher with july at 
1 a pound 
sugar futures fell in technically inspired selling in new york 
contracts settled 50 cent to 101 cents lower with october at 1346 
cents a pound 
gold and silver futures staged a strong rally on new yorks 
commodity exchange reacting to the inflationary cues of higher 
commodity prices and to the dollars pronounced weakness wednesday 
against other major currencies 
gold settled 730 to 8 higher with august at 38840 a troy 
ounce silver was 163 cents to 18 cents higher with july at 5393 
a troy ounce 
crudeoil futures advanced on the new york mercantile exchange 
amid labor uncertainties in the north sea oil field 
west texas intermediate crude oil settled 21 cents to 52 cents 
higher with august at 2079 a barrel heating oil was 90 cent to 
117 cents higher with august at 5106 cents a gallon unleaded 
gasoline was 05 cent to 35 cent lower with august at 5742 cents a 
gallon 
